"{\"uid\": \"thesouthafrican.com-sport-paris-olympics-2024-paris-olympics-2024-meet-south-africa-wrestling-team-breaking-nicolaas-de-lange-result\", \"text\": \"Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.  thesouthafrican.com is a division of Blue Sky Publications Ltd. Reproduction without permission prohibited  Home\\u00bbSport\\u00bbParis Olympics 2024\\u00bbParis Olympics 2024: Meet South Africa's WRESTLING team  South Africa will be represented by one competitor in wrestling competition at the Paris Olympics 2024. Get to know him better \\u2026  South Africa will be represented byonecompetitor inwrestlingcompetition at theParis Olympics 2024.  Bet Anytime, Anywhere Quick and Easy with Betway  Nicolaas de Langewill battle for the medals in the men's freestyle wrestling 97kg division.  For the latest Paris Olympics 2024 news, bookmarkThe South African website'sdedicated section  Wrestling is one of theoldest sports in human history- if not the oldest.  Multiple sculptures, reliefs and cave drawings - some of which date to around 15 000 years ago - show wrestlers using various holds that are still used in the present-day sport.  Wrestling was a key part of the ancient Olympic Games, where it was first contested in 708 BC.  Wrestling matches were organised as its own event in two disciplines ('upright' and 'ground' wrestling) and as part of the pentathlon.  Modern wrestling consists oftwoseparate disciplines:Greco-Romanwrestling, a wrestling style based on the ancient sport, andfreestylewrestling, a more modern format.  The two Olympic wrestling disciplines, each with its own rules.  In Greco-Roman wrestling, a competitor can only use his arms and upper body to attack his opponent above the waist.  Freestyle wrestling is a much more open form of the sport in which competitors also use their legs and can hold opponents above or below the waist.  However, the objective is the same in both styles.  Contested on a circular combat area, a bout consists of two three-minute periods.  Wrestlers must either use their bare hands to pin their opponent's two shoulders down to the mat without holding them by their singlet (this is called a 'fall') or, if no fall is secured during the bout, have the most points at the end of regulation time by performing takedown and reversal moves.  Greco-Romanwrestling has been a blue-ribbon Olympic event ever since the first modern Games were held in Athens in 1896. It became a permanent fixture on the Olympic programme in 1908.  Freestyle wrestling made its debut a few years later at the 1904 St. Louis Olympics and has featured on the Olympic programme ever since the Antwerp 1920 Games.  Women's freestyle wrestling has been on the Olympic programme since the 2004 Athens Olympics.  Athletes representing the Soviet Union have won 116 medals at the Games, including 62 golds. Team USA athletes have secured 142 medals (57 golds).  Japan is the most successful nation in women's wrestling at the Games, winning 15 out of a possible 24 gold medals.  The wrestling\\u00a0competitions at the\\u00a0Paris Olympics 2024\\u00a0are scheduled to run from5 to 11 AugustatGrand Palais \\u00c9ph\\u00e9m\\u00e8reinChamp de Mars.  As many as 290 wrestlers from 58 nations are expected to compete across 18 different weight categories.  The men will wrestle against each other in both freestyle and Greco-Roman\\u00a0events, whereas the women will only participate in the freestyle wrestling.  Sixteen wrestlers compete in each division.  The competition consists of a single-elimination tournament, with a repechage\\u00a0used to determine the winner of two bronze medals.  The two finalists will wrestle for the gold and silver medals.  Each wrestler losing to one of the two finalists moves into the repechage that culminates in a pair of bronze medal matches featuring the semi-final losers who each face the remaining repechage opponent from their half of the bracket.  South Africa hasneverwon a wrestling medal in its Olympic history.  As reported byThe South African website, theSouth African Sports Confederation, Olympic and Paralympic Committee (Sascoc)has confirmed the prize money on offer for any South African medal winners - as well as their coaches.  - Athletes who win gold will be awardedR400 000, with the coach receivingR100 000  - Silver medalists will earnR200 000andR50 000for the coach  - Bronze medal payouts will beR75 000andR25 000for the athlete and coach, respectively  Men:Nicolaas de Lange (97kg)  Coach/Manager:Jan Roets  WIN R2 000: Take The South African's SASSA Survey  The South African is hiring! Freelance writing positions available  Follow The South African on Facebook for the latest local and international news  Follow The South African's WhatsApp channel for the latest sport, lifestyle and local news  Follow The South African on X for the latest, breaking news  A brand new shopping mall is coming to Pretoria East, bringing major retailers and new convenience to the area.  Orlando Pirates are reportedly set to welcome a new staff member in former Stellenbosch FC Head of Recruitment Brendon Fourie.  Masindi Nemtajela was stretched off during Orlando Pirates' 6-0 win over TS Galaxy on Sunday afternoon in Mbombela.  IT support is not just technical, it is personal.  Liema Pantsi's victory was clouded as fans of the 'Big Brother Mzansi' show expressed that Smash Afrika was unprofessional towards her.  A dominant weekend for the SA teams in the URC has made a big impact on the latest log standings as the playoffs edge closer.    TheSouthAfrican.com is all about South Africa and the stories that affect South Africans, wherever they are in the world.  We are independent.No agenda.No bias.  Our offices are for administrative purposes only, no visitors will be accepted without an appointment.  South Africa- Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd - Registration Number: 2005/028472/07 - Address: Regus Business Centre, 1st Floor, Block B, North Park, Black River Park, 2 Fir Street, Observatory, Cape Town, 7925, South Africa  Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.\"}"